rComments: I loved this prof, he was so considerate for exams and allowed students input if the questions on the exams were not clear. You do need to study and the paper was graded hard but finishing his class with an A is doable !

Sa classe est bien organisé et ses attentes sont claires. Les examens théoriques sont pertinents mais il y a beaucoup de par coeur. J'ai beaucoup aimé le projet final sur les décisions disciplinaires de l'OIIO. C'est un professeur qui connait bien sa matière mais ton un peu monotone...
This professor is not so great. Unclear in his exam questions, and refuses to answer questions during the exam or during exam review. Just study hard and pray that you will make it through!

He's really nice, knowledgable person. For a class that is already boring he did an OK job. This whole class is memorization but very boring, alot of lists to remember and midterm and final have short answer questions + long, but i find impossible to get an A+ with him. There's a midterm and a project each worth 30% then a Final.

His classes were ok, his slides were useful and he followed the textbook well. A lot of questions in the tests about medications even after the initial med test. If you concentrate on slides for studying you will do ok.
